The Lagos State House of Assembly yesterday passed the 2019 Appropriation Bill. Governor Akinwumi Ambode had last December presented a budget proposal of N873,532 Billion, but the house increased it to N873, 532 billion. Capital expenditure stands at N479.691 billion; and the recurrent, N393.841 billion. The speaker of the house, Mudashiru Obasa, directed the Slerk, Azeez Sanni, to send a copy of the adopted appropriation bill to the governor for assent. Fiscal discipline: Only 22 states have presented 2019 budgets Gombe Assembly passes 2019 budget Ajimobi signs 2019 Appropriation Bill